    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-8">Why Consider Switching Your Swiss Health Insurance?</h2>
        
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 mb-8">
          <p>Each year, hundreds of thousands of individuals in Switzerland make the decision to switch health insurance or change health insurance providers. This isn't a random trend; it's a calculated move often driven by significant financial and personal factors. Many ask, "is it worth changing health insurance in Switzerland?" In a dynamic healthcare landscape like Switzerland's, staying informed and proactive about your insurance choices can lead to substantial benefits, including finding cheaper health insurance or better health insurance coverage.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Skyrocketing Premiums: The 2025 Reality</h3>
        
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 border-l-4 border-primary-500 mb-8">
          <div class="flex items-start mb-4">
            <div class="bg-primary-100 rounded-full p-3 mr-4">
              <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-primary-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Quest for Cheaper Health Insurance</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600">One of the most significant drivers for considering a health insurance switch in Switzerland is the persistent upward trend in premium costs. For 2025, forecasts indicate an average premium increase of around 6%. You might be wondering, "will premium increase in Zurich?" or "will premium increase in Geneva?" Yes, and in some cantons or with specific insurers, this figure could be even higher.</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mt-3">This isn't an isolated event; it follows a pattern of rising healthcare expenditures and insurance costs that directly impact household budgets across the country. For many, this annual ritual of premium hikes means that the plan which was cost-effective last year might no longer be the most economical choice, prompting the search for cheaper health insurance Switzerland.</p>
              <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4 my-4">
                <p class="text-yellow-800 m-0"><strong>Important:</strong> By comparing the new premium for your current plan against what other insurers offer for equivalent or even better health insurance coverage, you might find substantial annual savings, sometimes amounting to hundreds or even thousands of francs, depending on your family size and chosen coverage.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Your Life Changes, Your Insurance Should Too</h3>
        
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 mb-8">
          <p>Life is not static, and neither are your healthcare needs. What might have been the perfect health insurance plan when you first arrived in Switzerland, or a few years ago, may no longer align with your current circumstances. Several life changes can trigger the need to change health insurance:</p>
          
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-primary-500 mr-2" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M6.267 3.455a3.066 3.066 0 001.745-.723 3.066 3.066 0 013.976 0 3.066 3.066 0 001.745.723 3.066 3.066 0 012.812 2.812c.051.643.304 1.254.723 1.745a3.066 3.066 0 010 3.976 3.066 3.066 0 00-.723 1.745 3.066 3.066 0 01-2.812 2.812 3.066 3.066 0 00-1.745.723 3.066 3.066 0 01-3.976 0 3.066 3.066 0 00-1.745-.723 3.066 3.066 0 01-2.812-2.812 3.066 3.066 0 00-.723-1.745 3.066 3.066 0 010-3.976 3.066 3.066 0 00.723-1.745 3.066 3.066 0 012.812-2.812zm7.44 5.252a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                </svg>
                Changes in Health Status
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Perhaps your health has improved, and you no longer require extensive coverage, making a plan with a higher deductible and lower premium more attractive. Conversely, a new health condition might necessitate a plan with more comprehensive coverage, lower out-of-pocket costs, or better access to specific specialists or treatments.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 flex items-center">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-primary-500 mr-2" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
